meta {
  name: GET air-conditioning status
  type: http
  seq: 15
}

get {
  url: {{base_url}}/api/v2/air-conditioning/{{vin}}
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

docs {
  Skoda mysmob air-conditioning status. Provides climatisation state
  + target temperature + window-heating state + plug connection
  state (yes — chargerConnectionState lives here, not under
  /charging).

  Drives: climate entity, target_temperature, window_heating_front /
  _back binary sensors, plug_connected, connector_locked.

  Implementation: gathered in SkodaClient.get_status() at
  custom_components/vag_connect/cariad/api/skoda.py:153.

  Defensive: state="INVALID" / "OFF" / None all collapse to
  climatisation_active=False. v1.10.1 added safe_float for
  targetTemperature.temperatureValue (some EU firmwares ship
  "21,5" with a comma).

  v2.1.0 — also drives ``sensor.<vin>_climate_ready_at`` (TIMESTAMP)
  via the new ``estimatedDateTimeToReachTargetTemperature`` field
  (closes Scout reports #186 + #188). Field is only populated during
  active climate runs; sensor stays "unknown" when climatisation is OFF.
}
